1
00:00:01,070 --> 00:00:03,480
(Episode 66)

2
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:12,280
I hate to see you go,
but you should head in, Jang Mi.

3
00:00:15,790 --> 00:00:16,860
Baek Ho.

4
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:18,690
Actually, tomorrow...

5
00:00:19,190 --> 00:00:20,190
What?

6
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:32,140
What?

7
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:34,310
What's that?

8
00:00:34,870 --> 00:00:36,780
Why is that unfamiliar car parked there?

9
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,250
Could it be an accomplice?

10
00:00:52,620 --> 00:00:54,330
Baek Ho, what do we do?

11
00:00:55,230 --> 00:00:56,230
Wait...

12
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,230
Excuse me, why are you parked
in front of my house?

13
00:01:03,470 --> 00:01:04,570
Come out here right now!

14
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:32,660
Who in the world is that?

15
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,800
Why are they running away?

16
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:36,600
The license plate...

17
00:01:40,410 --> 00:01:41,410
Who was that?

18
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:51,620
Manager Lee, find out
whose car the number I just sent you...

19
00:01:51,850 --> 00:01:53,320
belongs to.

20
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:55,020
Yes, I'll look into it right away.

21
00:01:58,260 --> 00:01:59,260
What?

22
00:02:00,190 --> 00:02:02,860
It's Lawyer Kang Baek Ho's car.

23
00:02:03,130 --> 00:02:05,030
What? Kang Baek Ho?

24
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:08,700
Why did he drive off when he saw me?

25
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:09,770
Could it be...

26
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:12,200
that Kang Baek Ho knows something?

27
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,870
No, that's impossible.

28
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:17,180
Or was he leaving
after a meeting with Father?

29
00:02:18,180 --> 00:02:21,380
I heard a rumor that Kang Baek Ho
is joining the Dream Group Legal Team.

30
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:23,680
It looks like the Chairman
interviewed him personally.

31
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,820
Why does that old man have to interfere
with every little thing I do?

32
00:02:28,290 --> 00:02:30,620
It's trouble if Kang Baek Ho sees Seo Rin.

33
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,690
Why must he make things so complicated?

34
00:02:32,860 --> 00:02:35,190
I'll keep a close eye on Kang Baek Ho.

35
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:36,460
Good. Do that.

36
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:45,070
(Law Firm Leeho)

37
00:02:45,070 --> 00:02:46,910
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

38
00:02:47,610 --> 00:02:49,210
I looked in the rearview mirror,

39
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:51,840
and I think CEO Chae saw my license plate.

40
00:02:51,910 --> 00:02:54,610
She'll know it was you right away.
What do we do?

41
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:56,710
At least she didn't see us together.

42
00:02:56,950 --> 00:02:58,680
We just have to play dumb with CEO Chae
no matter what.

43
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:02,190
Anyway, Baek Ho.

44
00:03:02,990 --> 00:03:05,860
You know, having you this close to me...

45
00:03:06,290 --> 00:03:08,860
- puts my mind at ease.
- Really?

46
00:03:09,590 --> 00:03:10,600
Then I deserve a reward.

47
00:03:11,630 --> 00:03:13,200
Stop it.

48
00:03:13,930 --> 00:03:15,400
Come on.

49
00:03:15,670 --> 00:03:18,500
Are you just going to say thanks?
Is that it?

50
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:21,540
Come on, that's not fair.
I should get something for it.

51
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:22,710
Here.

52
00:03:23,540 --> 00:03:25,110
You're too much.

53
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:33,480
What? Hey, that's cheating!

54
00:03:33,550 --> 00:03:36,750
Hey, I didn't cheat.
I didn't even get a proper one.

55
00:03:36,820 --> 00:03:37,860
What was that?

56
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,220
Well then, should we try for real?

57
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:43,230
Just so you know,
I am never giving you a reward again.

58
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,500
I'm so scared.

59
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:47,700
Anyway,

60
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:49,830
I guess I can't take you
all the way home today.

61
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:52,670
Will you be okay on your own?
I'll get you a taxi.

62
00:03:54,410 --> 00:03:56,870
We can't risk Chae Hwa Young seeing us.

63
00:03:56,980 --> 00:03:59,880
I think we should be careful
about coming to my house from now on.

64
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,100
Seo Rin.

65
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:29,770
Who were you with until now?

66
00:04:30,110 --> 00:04:33,240
What? Why do you care who I see?

67
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:36,050
I saw Lawyer Kang Baek Ho's car
in front of our house earlier,

68
00:04:36,310 --> 00:04:38,020
but he sped off the moment he saw me.

69
00:04:38,580 --> 00:04:39,680
Really?

70
00:04:40,180 --> 00:04:42,050
And? So what?

71
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:45,920
Were you by any chance
meeting Lawyer Kang?

72
00:04:46,860 --> 00:04:50,160
What are you talking about?
Why would I meet Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

73
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,400
You know General Manager Kang Jun Ho
is coming tomorrow evening, right?

74
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:56,200
Be home early tomorrow.

75
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:58,900
I think I'll just leave
when General Manager Kang...

76
00:04:58,900 --> 00:04:59,970
gets here tomorrow.

77
00:05:01,540 --> 00:05:03,940
I told you I didn't want to marry him.

78
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:05,340
Honestly, you...

79
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:07,310
Are you going to keep being so difficult?

80
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,960
Something's not right.

81
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:24,560
She doesn't seem like my Seo Rin.

82
00:05:27,130 --> 00:05:28,130
Unless...

83
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:31,240
What if she's actually Oh Jang Mi?

84
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,240
I'll have to check first thing tomorrow.

85
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:42,580
(Korea University Hospital)

86
00:06:07,810 --> 00:06:09,370
If she has a mole behind her ear,

87
00:06:10,270 --> 00:06:11,680
then I'll know she's the real Seo Rin.

88
00:06:13,310 --> 00:06:15,350
I should have checked sooner.

89
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,560
What's this?

90
00:06:34,270 --> 00:06:37,370
Did she get a scar from the accident
right where the mole used to be?

91
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:41,510
Now there's no way to know.

92
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,340
Tok Hee needs her breakfast.

93
00:06:44,710 --> 00:06:47,750
Mom, she's sleeping.
How is she supposed to eat?

94
00:06:49,210 --> 00:06:51,950
Tok Hee is thirsty. She wants some water.

95
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,720
Okay, Mom. You go on in.

96
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:56,820
- I'll go buy some water.
- Okay.

97
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:01,990
What?

98
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:06,430
What?

99
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,200
What?

100
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:18,980
Oh! A burglar!

101
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:23,950
Wait, no. It's a burglar!
A burglar is here!

102
00:07:28,650 --> 00:07:30,290
A burglar! There's a burglar!

103
00:07:30,290 --> 00:07:32,690
It's a burglar! What do I do?

104
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:34,890
A burglar! There's a burglar here!

105
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,130
What? You let the blackmailer get away?

106
00:07:41,670 --> 00:07:43,430
What a shame.

107
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:45,070
I'm so upset that I could just scream.

108
00:07:45,470 --> 00:07:48,170
That blackmailer had the video footage...

109
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,910
that showed CEO Chae Hwa Young
driving my dad to his death.

110
00:07:49,970 --> 00:07:52,580
You had him right in your grasp.

111
00:07:53,010 --> 00:07:54,510
That's terrible.

112
00:07:55,910 --> 00:07:59,920
Somehow, I have to find him again
and make her pay for what she did.

113
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:00,990
Of course.

114
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:06,160
What? Wait, Baek Ho is joining
the Dream Hotel Legal Team?

115
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:09,630
It seems Team Leader Jin Hong Ju
recommended him to Chairman Ma.

116
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:11,060
That kid, Kang Baek Ho...

117
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:14,770
Why would he go there
when he was doing fine working with you?

118
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:17,770
- Tell him he can't go.
- What do you mean, he can't?

119
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:21,170
Chairman Ma of Dream Group
already okayed it,

120
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:23,640
and Baek Ho is on his way to meet him now.

121
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:27,350
- Already?
- Yes. It's what he wants, too.

122
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:33,950
Seriously, what am I in this family?
Am I even the man of the house?

123
00:08:34,620 --> 00:08:38,190
What are you talking about?
Of course you're the man of the house.

124
00:08:38,260 --> 00:08:42,360
But you completely ignored my opinion
on such an important decision...

125
00:08:42,430 --> 00:08:44,630
and took care of it
in the blink of an eye?

126
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:47,930
I think you're the one who's got it wrong.

127
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,400
Baek Ho is a grown man.

128
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,540
He's old enough
to make his own decisions for his future.

129
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:55,310
For crying out loud!

130
00:08:55,670 --> 00:08:59,610
Jun Ho works there, and now his brother?
What are people going to say?

131
00:08:59,810 --> 00:09:03,480
Won't they say our whole family is just
leeching off the Dream Group?

132
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,450
Leeching?

133
00:09:06,550 --> 00:09:09,950
He's a very skilled lawyer.
They're the ones who scouted him.

134
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:12,560
And that's not all.

135
00:09:12,860 --> 00:09:16,490
What about our Jun Ho,
who's engaged to CEO Chae's daughter?

136
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:19,760
Everyone is going to be so envious
of our family.

137
00:09:19,930 --> 00:09:21,930
Don't be ridiculous.

138
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:23,670
As if Chairman Ma's family...

139
00:09:23,770 --> 00:09:27,000
would ever let their granddaughter
marry Jun Ho.

140
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:30,170
You're just giving Jun Ho false hope.

141
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:33,310
Look, I've made myself clear.
I am against this marriage.

142
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:34,450
Understood?

143
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:36,550
What's the use...

144
00:09:37,350 --> 00:09:40,280
Gosh, what's gotten into him?

145
00:09:41,050 --> 00:09:42,490
He's getting stranger by the day.

146
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:47,530
Good morning.

147
00:09:58,540 --> 00:10:02,010
Jang Mi, I think CEO Chae
stopped by Seo Rin's room.

148
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:12,050
I figured as much.
Thanks for the heads-up.

149
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:25,900
Gosh.

150
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:30,030
I knew you were talented,
but that looks like a real scar.

151
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:34,640
Right? All those odd jobs I used to do
are finally paying off.

152
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:37,210
Wait, so you've even worked part-time jobs
like this before?

153
00:10:37,510 --> 00:10:40,380
Yes, I did some work
as a special effects makeup assistant.

154
00:10:41,210 --> 00:10:42,680
How's it look? Convincing, right?

155
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,380
Yes, it's absolutely flawless.

156
00:10:44,820 --> 00:10:48,020
Even if CEO Chae checks for the mole,
she'll never be able to tell.

157
00:10:48,350 --> 00:10:50,350
But about Seo Rin...

158
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:52,490
How long is she going to be like this?

159
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:56,460
She's not going to stay
like this forever, is she?

160
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:57,900
Right?

161
00:10:58,630 --> 00:11:00,560
No, that won't happen.

162
00:11:03,970 --> 00:11:05,600
Good morning.

163
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,410
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

164
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:10,010
You're in a good mood, Team Leader Jin.

165
00:11:10,210 --> 00:11:11,480
Of course I am.

166
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:16,050
With Lawyer Kang Baek Ho joining our team,
I have every reason to be.

167
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:17,750
The Legal Team?

168
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,120
Why?

169
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,850
You haven't heard yet.

170
00:11:28,730 --> 00:11:29,990
Are you at the office?

171
00:11:29,990 --> 00:11:33,160
Baek Ho, are you really joining
the Legal Team?

172
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:35,000
Yes. I'll see you later.

173
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,040
Who are you texting
so early in the morning?

174
00:11:42,770 --> 00:11:46,110
Mind your own business and do your job,
Team Leader Jin.

175
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:51,250
Goodness.

176
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:54,690
So you just came
from Oh Jang Mi's hospital room?

177
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:55,990
Yes.

178
00:11:56,650 --> 00:12:00,320
I went to see if the person in that bed
was really Oh Jang Mi.

179
00:12:01,130 --> 00:12:04,960
Because if she has a mole behind her ear,
she's not Oh Jang Mi. She's my Seo Rin.

180
00:12:05,260 --> 00:12:07,830
So, were you able to check
for a mole behind her ear?

181
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:12,240
As if her facial scars weren't enough,
she had one behind her ear too.

182
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,500
Of all places.

183
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:14,940
But, ma'am...

184
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:18,640
Why are you so suspicious of the Seo Rin
who's living with you now?

185
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:20,510
You don't think it's her?

186
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:23,950
It feels that way.
Something just feels off.

187
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:28,790
She doesn't seem like the old Seo Rin,
and things just don't add up.

188
00:12:29,690 --> 00:12:31,960
Refusing to marry Jun Ho, for one thing.

189
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:34,390
She used to be so crazy about Jun Ho...

190
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:41,670
Chairman, what brings you here?

191
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:44,070
I'm here...

192
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:48,770
to introduce a new lawyer
for our group's Legal Team.

193
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:52,080
The Dream Group's Legal Team?

194
00:12:59,650 --> 00:13:01,050
My name is Kang Baek Ho, and I'm a lawyer.

195
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:03,520
Though I'm sure you already recognize me.

196
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:05,820
You're joining the Legal Team?

197
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,320
No way.

198
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:10,900
If he meets Seo Rin,
he'll immediately suspect they're twins.

199
00:13:13,530 --> 00:13:16,200
Is this your handiwork again,
Team Leader Jin?

200
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,600
Excuse me?

201
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:21,240
- No, that's not...
- I recruited him because I need him.

202
00:13:22,410 --> 00:13:23,410
Father.

203
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:27,340
How could you make a decision like this
without saying a word to me?

204
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:30,810
If you did this just based on
what Team Leader Jin said...

205
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:32,020
What are you talking about?

206
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:34,820
I have the final say on personnel
for this group.

207
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:38,490
And I don't want to drag this out,

208
00:13:38,890 --> 00:13:42,060
but I noticed Team Leader Jin's desk
still hasn't been put back.

209
00:13:43,830 --> 00:13:46,930
Forgive my interruption,
but may I say something?

210
00:13:47,570 --> 00:13:48,870
Yes, Lawyer Kang.

211
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,070
Removing her desk,
regardless of the reason,

212
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:54,540
is a serious human rights violation
and constitutes workplace harassment.

213
00:13:54,770 --> 00:13:55,910
Lawyer Kang.

214
00:13:56,570 --> 00:13:58,410
You just got here.
What makes you think you can interfere?

215
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:03,880
Chairman, I have an external meeting
I need to rush to.

216
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:06,080
I understand your concerns,

217
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:09,190
so I'll take care of the issue
with Team Leader Jin on my way out.

218
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:11,060
Fine, you're excused.

219
00:14:11,490 --> 00:14:14,890
Don't mind me.
I only came to introduce Lawyer Kang.

220
00:14:15,490 --> 00:14:16,960
Just now, right out front,

221
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:19,400
I had him introduce himself
to Director Ma.

222
00:14:20,330 --> 00:14:22,200
Kang Baek Ho saw Seo Rin?

223
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:24,440
Grandfather.

224
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:28,870
- Yes?
- Chairman, I will take my leave then.

225
00:14:28,940 --> 00:14:31,210
Alright. You should stay and have a meal
with us later.

226
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:40,850
Grandfather, seeing you at the office
makes me even happier.

227
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:46,960
I guess Kang Baek Ho didn't say anything.

228
00:14:51,830 --> 00:14:52,830
Father.

229
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,770
I mean, Chairman. Thank you.

230
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:03,440
Grandfather,
Team Leader Jin really went through a lot.

231
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:06,840
But don't tell me
you came all this way just for that.

232
00:15:06,910 --> 00:15:07,950
Of course not.

233
00:15:08,650 --> 00:15:12,780
Your grandfather just came to see
how his dear Seo Rin is doing at work.

234
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:14,690
Really, Grandfather?

235
00:15:14,890 --> 00:15:17,790
We have work to do,
so you'll have to leave us to it.

236
00:15:17,890 --> 00:15:21,130
With CEO Chae away,
who will make sure no one is slacking off?

237
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:22,230
Me.

238
00:15:23,090 --> 00:15:25,730
My Director Ma is certainly
pulling her weight.

239
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,260
Good. That's how it should be.

240
00:15:29,030 --> 00:15:30,970
You being here is such a big help,
Grandfather.

241
00:15:43,810 --> 00:15:45,450
Is everything to your liking?

242
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:46,650
- Yes, it's delicious.
- Yes, it's great.

243
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:50,990
The salad bar is over there,
so please help yourselves.

244
00:15:50,990 --> 00:15:52,020
Yes, thank you.

245
00:15:52,820 --> 00:15:55,660
Tae Sook, you're much nicer than you were.

246
00:15:55,660 --> 00:15:56,960
Does becoming the boss do that to people?

247
00:15:57,900 --> 00:15:58,900
Excuse me!

248
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:00,300
Be right there.

249
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,340
Mom, since we're here,
should we grab a bite?

250
00:16:05,370 --> 00:16:08,640
- Let's have shabu-shabu.
- Yummy! Shabu-shabu sounds great.

251
00:16:09,070 --> 00:16:11,610
Let's sit over there. Let's go.

252
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:15,850
What made you decide
to join the Legal Team?

253
00:16:16,010 --> 00:16:18,950
I had to if I wanted
to stay close and protect you.

254
00:16:19,020 --> 00:16:21,020
What? You came here for me?

255
00:16:21,890 --> 00:16:23,590
That's part of it,

256
00:16:24,690 --> 00:16:26,760
but I also want to find out
the truth about my father.

257
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:31,660
I need to know how he was involved
in your father's death.

258
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:33,760
I have to get my hands on
the critical evidence.

259
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:37,130
And as his son, I have a duty
to bring the full truth to light.

260
00:16:37,370 --> 00:16:39,370
Chae Hwa Young is no pushover.

261
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:41,070
You need to be careful, Baek Ho.

262
00:16:41,070 --> 00:16:43,810
That's all the more reason
I need to be by your side.

263
00:16:44,780 --> 00:16:46,040
Don't say things like that.

264
00:16:49,380 --> 00:16:50,550
I love you, Jang Mi.

265
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:53,550
What? Where did that come from?

266
00:16:54,590 --> 00:16:56,850
When I thought you'd fallen into a coma,

267
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,360
do you know what my biggest regret was?

268
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:04,030
Not telling you that
I love you more often.

269
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,660
Not showing you how much I care.

270
00:17:09,170 --> 00:17:11,170
That was my biggest regret.

271
00:17:14,770 --> 00:17:15,810
Oh, right.

272
00:17:16,510 --> 00:17:19,640
What if someone hears you?
This is the office.

273
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:20,940
There are eyes and ears everywhere.

274
00:17:21,410 --> 00:17:22,410
All right.

275
00:17:23,980 --> 00:17:25,220
Control yourself, Kang Baek Ho.

276
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:29,720
By the way,

277
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:31,390
Chae Hwa Young is having
General Manager Kang...

278
00:17:31,390 --> 00:17:32,790
over to the house later.

279
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:34,090
She invited my brother?

280
00:17:34,190 --> 00:17:37,360
Yes. Chae Hwa Young is pushing for me
and General Manager Kang to get married.

281
00:17:37,430 --> 00:17:39,360
- What should I do?
- What do you mean?

282
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:41,200
Absolutely not. Okay?

283
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:42,430
Of course.

284
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,000
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

285
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,810
What? Baek Ho joined the Legal Team?

286
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:54,280
Yes. A spot opened up
right after Lawyer Kim quit.

287
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:58,220
- Really?
- But by any chance,

288
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:00,750
are you and Director Ma
on good terms these days?

289
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:03,920
- What?
- It's just, lately, it's been strange.

290
00:18:04,390 --> 00:18:07,160
It seems like Director Ma
and Baek Ho have gotten closer.

291
00:18:09,230 --> 00:18:12,230
Director Ma and my brother
are getting close?

292
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:15,130
Yes. And I can't figure out
for the life of me why.

293
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:18,900
Do you know why?

294
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,470
Lately, Baek Ho kept...

295
00:18:21,070 --> 00:18:23,510
asking me to arrange a meeting
with Director Ma,

296
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,740
but this is the first time that
I'm hearing of them being close.

297
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:29,780
Oh, my. So you really didn't know.

298
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:33,620
Just the other day, Director Ma
took a call from Baek Ho and rushed out.

299
00:18:33,980 --> 00:18:36,020
I've even seen the two of them
together several times.

300
00:18:36,950 --> 00:18:37,960
Really?

301
00:18:42,490 --> 00:18:43,890
Is Kang Baek Ho still at the office?

302
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,800
Yes, it seems so.

303
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,700
We need to keep a close eye on him.

304
00:18:47,930 --> 00:18:51,440
It'd be a problem if he told Seo Rin
anything about being a twin.

305
00:18:55,570 --> 00:18:56,570
Here she comes.

306
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:59,640
What are you doing?
What do you want to ask me?

307
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:03,050
Director Ma, it's just that
you look exactly like someone I know.

308
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:06,080
What are you talking about?
Who do I look like?

309
00:19:06,220 --> 00:19:07,850
Get out of my way. Stop being so annoying.

310
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:10,490
Excuse me, do you happen to know
a woman named Oh Jang Mi?

311
00:19:10,790 --> 00:19:11,990
Who is Oh Jang Mi?

312
00:19:11,990 --> 00:19:13,560
- It's just you two could be twins.
- Stop.

313
00:19:15,390 --> 00:19:16,560
Will you all just stop it?

314
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:18,630
Mom.

315
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:21,130
What's all this commotion at the office?

316
00:19:21,470 --> 00:19:23,170
I have a splitting headache as it is.

317
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:26,970
He's making a scene,
going on about how I look like someone.

318
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:30,840
Look. If you're into me, just say so.

319
00:19:30,910 --> 00:19:32,640
I won't bite your head off for it.

320
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:35,080
But did you think this...

321
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:37,850
cheesy "you look like someone" act
would work on me?

322
00:19:37,950 --> 00:19:40,750
Unbelievable.
Talk about being full of yourself.

323
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:44,520
For your information,
I'm deeply in love with someone else.

324
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,920
How can you be so confidently
wrong about this?

325
00:19:46,990 --> 00:19:48,960
Stop. That's enough.

326
00:19:49,290 --> 00:19:50,660
Seo Rin, that goes for you too.

327
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,800
Lawyer Kang, I'd like a word with you.

328
00:19:54,300 --> 00:19:57,600
Yes. As a matter of fact,
I had something to ask you.

329
00:19:57,670 --> 00:19:58,670
This is perfect timing.

330
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:03,540
I figured out one thing for sure.

331
00:20:03,610 --> 00:20:06,610
Your personality is absolutely nothing
like the woman I love.

332
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:15,750
What did you want to ask me?

333
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:17,490
I'll get straight to the point.

334
00:20:18,390 --> 00:20:22,860
Did you approach Jang Mi
because she resembled Director Ma Seo Rin?

335
00:20:23,330 --> 00:20:25,700
- I'm curious to know why.
- "Approached?"

336
00:20:26,930 --> 00:20:28,000
Did I misspeak?

337
00:20:28,970 --> 00:20:30,370
Then let's say "befriended."

338
00:20:31,470 --> 00:20:32,600
Please, answer my question.

339
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,770
When you saw Jang Mi, who looks identical
to Director Ma Seo Rin,

340
00:20:36,310 --> 00:20:38,010
what went through your mind?

341
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:40,840
You're that curious, are you?

342
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:45,720
Yes. I've been wondering why
you've been so kind to Jang Mi.

343
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:51,320
At first, it was because she looked
so much like Seo Rin that it was uncanny.

344
00:20:51,490 --> 00:20:52,790
So I met with her a few times, that's all.

345
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:55,790
But they turned out to be
completely different.

346
00:20:56,830 --> 00:20:58,730
Everything from her personality
to her tastes.

347
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:02,900
You've met Seo Rin yourself,
so you must know.

348
00:21:03,030 --> 00:21:04,670
When I first met Ma Seo Rin,

349
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:07,840
I almost thought that
my Jang Mi had woken up.

350
00:21:09,270 --> 00:21:14,240
They say everyone has someone out there
who looks just like them.

351
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:15,910
A doppelganger.

352
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:22,050
You and my Seo Rin were introduced
at the reopening party, weren't you?

353
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:24,420
That's right.

354
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:26,760
But that was before I knew Jang Mi well.

355
00:21:28,890 --> 00:21:30,090
You're right.

356
00:21:31,460 --> 00:21:34,460
They may look alike,
but they're completely different.

357
00:21:35,230 --> 00:21:36,800
Their personalities
and even the way they talk...

358
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:42,670
I guess they're just two people
who happen to look alike.

359
00:21:50,450 --> 00:21:51,620
Honey.

360
00:21:51,820 --> 00:21:53,820
It's about CEO Chae.

361
00:21:54,350 --> 00:21:56,890
Based on what I heard from Hong Ju,

362
00:21:57,650 --> 00:22:00,590
I think she's caught up in something bad.

363
00:22:01,220 --> 00:22:03,460
Or maybe she's being blackmailed.

364
00:22:04,730 --> 00:22:06,160
Pretend you don't know anything.

365
00:22:07,330 --> 00:22:08,500
That's the best way to help her.

366
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:13,040
Oh my. Does that mean
you've known this whole time?

367
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:15,540
Before we go to that fashion show tonight,

368
00:22:16,810 --> 00:22:19,740
how about we go out for a nice dinner?

369
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,580
I'd love that.

370
00:22:23,310 --> 00:22:25,820
Should we go to that steakhouse
we went to the other day?

371
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:29,290
- Their steaks were amazing.
- Sure, whatever you want.

372
00:22:29,690 --> 00:22:31,790
Mrs. Yeom, go ahead
and make a reservation.

373
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:34,420
Yes, honey.

374
00:22:46,270 --> 00:22:48,110
I'll handle the seasoning.

375
00:22:48,510 --> 00:22:51,270
No, it's fine. I want to prepare this
for our guest myself.

376
00:22:51,710 --> 00:22:55,650
- You've set the table, right?
- Yes, it's a magnificent spread.

377
00:22:55,980 --> 00:22:58,280
All we need now is
the kimchi stew you made.

378
00:23:01,950 --> 00:23:02,950
Oh?

379
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,790
Looks like Jun Ho's here.

380
00:23:16,070 --> 00:23:17,430
Welcome, General Manager Kang.

381
00:23:18,570 --> 00:23:19,840
My son, Jun Ho.

382
00:23:20,370 --> 00:23:21,540
Good evening, ma'am.

383
00:23:26,110 --> 00:23:27,310
Right. Seo Rin?

384
00:23:27,780 --> 00:23:29,580
Seo Rin, what's taking you so long?
Come down.

385
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:37,290
- You're here.
- Thank you for having me.

386
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:38,760
It wasn't my idea.

387
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,930
She's just saying that because she's shy.

388
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:43,660
Please, have a seat.

389
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:47,800
Seo Rin. These are for you.

390
00:23:48,330 --> 00:23:49,400
Oh my.

391
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:51,330
Are these for me?

392
00:23:51,470 --> 00:23:53,470
You look great with roses.

393
00:23:55,040 --> 00:23:58,240
You're supposed to say I'm prettier
than the flowers. You're no fun.

394
00:23:59,540 --> 00:24:01,340
Thanks, though.

395
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:05,150
Where is the Chairman and your family?

396
00:24:05,150 --> 00:24:06,420
She sent them all away.

397
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:10,450
She said she wanted a nice dinner
with just the three of us.

398
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:11,820
She did?

399
00:24:12,990 --> 00:24:16,460
Today, I've invited you
as a prospective son-in-law.

400
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:34,340
She's completely ignoring me
and only has eyes for him.

401
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:36,610
What's up with Chae Hwa Young?

402
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:50,060
I hope the kimchi stew
is seasoned all right.

403
00:24:51,330 --> 00:24:53,500
Yes, it's delicious.

404
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:55,670
Really?

405
00:24:56,100 --> 00:25:00,140
I got the recipe from Lawyer Han
and made it myself.

406
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:03,210
I heard you liked kimchi stew.

407
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:05,540
Thank you.

408
00:25:05,780 --> 00:25:08,910
Unbelievable! You made this yourself, Mom?

409
00:25:11,380 --> 00:25:12,850
Pigs must be flying.

410
00:25:13,020 --> 00:25:15,350
Of course. General Manager Kang
is my future son-in-law.

411
00:25:15,620 --> 00:25:17,720
It's a mother-in-law's job
to dote on her son-in-law.

412
00:25:23,460 --> 00:25:27,000
Dad, why did Jun Ho go over
to Chairman Ma's?

413
00:25:28,100 --> 00:25:31,640
Your mother practically forced him to go,
didn't she?

414
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,710
Your mother is absolutely convinced that
your brother will be their son-in-law.

415
00:25:35,710 --> 00:25:36,770
Wait, son-in-law?

416
00:25:37,070 --> 00:25:39,810
So she's really trying to make Jun Ho
marry Director Ma Seo Rin?

417
00:25:39,940 --> 00:25:42,380
That will absolutely never happen.

418
00:25:42,710 --> 00:25:45,020
Right. There's no way that will happen.

419
00:25:49,850 --> 00:25:52,120
How about a glass of the wine
General Manager Kang brought?

420
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:54,120
Sure, why not?

421
00:25:57,090 --> 00:26:00,560
Seo Rin, you could play the violin for us.
It's been a while.

422
00:26:01,100 --> 00:26:02,430
You'd like that, wouldn't you, Seo Rin?

423
00:26:03,470 --> 00:26:04,500
The violin?

424
00:26:04,940 --> 00:26:06,270
Yes, the violin.

425
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:10,170
Our Seo Rin is an accomplished violinist,
you know.

426
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:15,050
I wonder if she can
actually play the violin.

427
00:26:15,980 --> 00:26:17,880
Seo Rin would have no problem.

428
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:19,350
But if she's actually Oh Jang Mi,

429
00:26:20,150 --> 00:26:21,350
there is no way.

430
00:26:21,990 --> 00:26:25,360
I have to get to the bottom
of this weird, nagging suspicion.

431
00:26:35,930 --> 00:26:38,640
I wonder how things are going
with my Jang Mi and Jun Ho.

432
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,900
That CEO Chae, seriously.

433
00:26:41,270 --> 00:26:43,740
Why is she trying to make my Jang Mi
marry Jun Ho?

434
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:45,410
It really pisses me off.

435
00:26:48,450 --> 00:26:50,710
Baek Ho. Hong Ju's here. Come on out.

436
00:26:50,710 --> 00:26:52,380
Why is Hong Ju at our house
all of a sudden?

437
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:54,550
We had dinner out together.

438
00:26:54,820 --> 00:26:56,950
We really hit it off, so on our way here,

439
00:26:56,950 --> 00:26:59,620
I insisted she come in for a cup of tea.

440
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,390
Mom, come on.

441
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:03,830
How could you invite her
over at this hour without telling me?

442
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:05,860
Come out, okay? And don't give me any lip.

443
00:27:19,980 --> 00:27:23,050
What are you doing, Seo Rin?
Go on, play something for us.

444
00:27:26,620 --> 00:27:29,120
Prove to me that you're not Oh Jang Mi.

445
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:01,520
(The First Man)

446
00:28:01,580 --> 00:28:03,120
Keep a close eye on Oh Tae Pyung, too.

447
00:28:03,490 --> 00:28:05,920
It looks like Oh Tae Pyung
is the blackmailer.

448
00:28:06,090 --> 00:28:08,760
Time for me to get on the case
and find out for myself.

449
00:28:09,090 --> 00:28:10,590
Jin Hong Ju, what brings you here?

450
00:28:10,890 --> 00:28:13,600
That's no way to talk to a guest.

451
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:16,730
Instead, could you give me a ride home,
Baek Ho?

452
00:28:17,130 --> 00:28:19,240
You're saying Seo Rin
was good at the violin?

453
00:28:19,370 --> 00:28:21,500
This is no time to worry about that.

454
00:28:21,570 --> 00:28:24,440
Well? Are you just going to stand there?

455
00:28:28,850 --> 00:28:30,850
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
